                         Time Complexity
Time Complexity =
        👉 Program run aaga evalo time edukkum nu measure pannradhu
        (based on input size n)
        💡 Big-O notation use pannitu explain pannuvom.
        Big-O = Worst case time (maximum time edukkura situation)

   🔹 Why Big-O important?
           Computer fast / slow nu depend pannadhu
           Algorithm smart-aa irukka illaya nu depend pannum
           Interview-la romba important 💼

   🔹 Real Life Example 🚶‍♂️
          📌 Class-la oru student-a thedra situation

Method 1:
           Oru oru student-aa check pannradhu
           👉 Time increases as students increase
Method 2:
           Roll number order-la irundha
           👉 Middle-la check pannalam

   👉 Same problem, different speed → Time Complexity 🔥
   🔹 Big-O Rules (Easy Memory)
               1️⃣ Constants ignore pannalam
               2️⃣ Worst case mattum consider pannalam
               3️⃣ Growth matter, exact time illa


      Order of time complexity : fast to Slow
               O(1)
               O(log n)
               O(n)
               O(n log n)
               O(n²)
               O(2ⁿ)
               O(n!)
